{"id":624554601,"lang":"csharp","lang_name":"C#","time":"1 year, 11 months","timestamp":1642758465,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"208 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/624554601/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Integer to Roman","memory":"36.5 MB","code":"public class Solution {\n    public string IntToRoman(int number) {\n        var map = new Dictionary<int, string>\n            {\n                {1, \"I\"},\n                {4, \"IV\"},\n                {5, \"V\"},\n                {9,\"IX\"},\n                {10,\"X\"},\n                {40,\"XL\"},\n                {50,\"L\"},\n                {90,\"XC\"},\n                {100,\"C\"},\n                {400,\"CD\"},\n                {500,\"D\"},\n                {900,\"CM\"},\n                {1000,\"M\"},\n            };\n\n            \n            var output = string.Empty;\n\n            for (int i = map.Count - 1; i >= 0; i--)\n            {\n                var item = map.ElementAt(i);\n                if (item.Key <= number)\n                {\n                    var j = i;\n                    while (number != 0)\n                    {\n                        var referenceNumber = item.Key;\n                        while (number >= referenceNumber)\n                        {\n                            number -= referenceNumber;\n                            output += item.Value;\n                        }\n\n                        if (j == 0)\n                        {\n                            break;\n                        }\n\n                        item = map.ElementAt(--j);\n                    }\n\n                    break;\n                }\n            }\n        return output;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"integer-to-roman","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
